<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: HOWARD REAPPOINTED TO STATE COASTAL PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Burbank City Councilwoman Mary Lou Howard has been reappointed to the 12-member 
state Coastal Commission by the state Senate Rules Committee, officials 
announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The reappointment was effective in May. Howard, 52, was first appointed to the 
commission in May, 1987. 
</P>
<P>
Howard also represents the commission on the Santa Monica Mountains 
Conservancy. 
</P>
<P>
The state Coastal Act directs the commission to balance development interests 
and protection of the coast as it reviews coast development permits. 
</P>
<P>
Howard was first elected to the Burbank council in 1979 and is in the middle of 
her third four-year term. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
