<HEADLINE>
<P>
 COOK IT LIGHT: SEAFOOD IN REDUCED-CALORIE SAUCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNE JONES, Jones is a food consultant and a cookbook author. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DEAR JEANNE: I'm interested in cutting the cholesterol in this seafood recipe 
without losing its wonderful flavor. 
</P>
<P>
 -- RUTH, San Antonio 
</P>
<P>
SEAFOOD IN CREAM SAUCE 
</P>
<P>
2 pounds scallops 
</P>
<P>
1/2 cup dry vermouth 
</P>
<P>
1 cube chicken bouillon 
</P>
<P>
1 cup whipping cream 
</P>
<P>
1/4 cup butter 
</P>
<P>
2 tablespoons flour 
</P>
<P>
1/2 pound mushrooms, sauteed, optional 
</P>
<P>
Bring scallops, vermouth and chicken bouillon to boil. Cover and simmer 2 
minutes. Remove scallops. 
</P>
<P>
Cook liquid until reduced by 1/2. Add whipping cream and boil until thick. 
</P>
<P>
Add butter and flour and cook until thick. Pour sauce over scallops and heat at 
450 degrees 10 minutes. Add sauteed mushrooms. Makes 4 servings. 
</P>
<P>
DEAR RUTH: I have made some adjustments that cut the cholesterol by more than 
half and greatly reduce the amount of fat and calories. 
</P>
<P>
Although I have included nutritional information for four servings, I think the 
recipe can easily serve six, especially with the added mushrooms, which flavor 
the sauce nicely. Try serving my version of seafood in cream sauce over your 
favorite pasta. 
</P>
<P>
 -- JEANNE 
</P>
<P>
LIGHTER SEAFOOD IN CREAM SAUCE 
</P>
<P>
2 pounds scallops 
</P>
<P>
1/2 cup chicken stock 
</P>
<P>
1/2 cup dry vermouth 
</P>
<P>
1/2 pound mushrooms, sliced 
</P>
<P>
1 cup evaporated skim milk 
</P>
<P>
1 tablespoon corn-oil margarine 
</P>
<P>
2 tablespoons unbleached flour 
</P>
<P>
Bring scallops, chicken stock and vermouth to boil. Cover and simmer 2 minutes. 
Remove scallops and add mushrooms to liquid. Boil over high heat 10 minutes. 
Add evaporated skim milk and boil 5 more minutes, until thick. 
</P>
<P>
Reduce heat to low. Add margarine and flour and stir with wire whisk several 
minutes until thickened. Pour sauce over scallops and heat at 450 degrees 10 
minutes. Makes 4 (1-cup) servings. 
</P>
<P>
Each serving contains approximately: 
</P>
<P>
Original Recipe: 
</P>
<P>
Calories: 495 
</P>
<P>
Cholesterol: 178 mg 
</P>
<P>
Fat: 31 gm 
</P>
<P>
Sodium: 805 mg 
</P>
<P>
Revised Recipe: 
</P>
<P>
Calories: 294 
</P>
<P>
Cholesterol: 82 mg 
</P>
<P>
Fat: 4 gm 
</P>
<P>
Sodium: 702 mg 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Recipe 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA083189-0066 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 101432 </DOCID>
