<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Cinema Corp.: The Chestnut Hill, Mass., theater chain said 
third-quarter net income rose 15% to $25.6 million while revenue advanced 21% 
to $491.3 million. The 1988 results included after-tax earnings of $19.3 
million from discontinued operations, which consist of its soft-drink bottling 
business that was sold March 23, 1989. The firm attributed the gains to 
improved performances by its theater division and Neiman Marcus Group, a 
59.9%-owned subsidiary whose results are consolidated with a lag of one 
quarter. 
</P>
