<P>
SECURITY AT PARK LABREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction crews have erected three guardhouses and set up gates and fences 
for a new security system at Park Labrea, the vast apartment complex east of 
Fairfax Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
Although much of the equipment has been installed and many residents have been 
issued decals for their automobiles, operation of the security system is not 
expected to begin until November or December, a spokesman for Park Labrea 
management said. 
</P>
<P>
The $1-million-plus program will close off most of the streets in the 
4,212-unit complex to all but residents and their guests. 
</P>
<P>
Residents will be able to enter by any of 11 automatic gates, and security 
guards will clear guests at the three checkpoints. 
