AUSTRIAN TRAINS COLLIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VIENNA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two passenger trains collided head-on in western Austria on Wednesday, killing 
at least one person and injuring 27 others, a railway spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Three cars derailed when the trains crashed while traveling at relatively low 
speeds between Bregenz, capital of Voralberg province, and the small town of 
Wolfurt, the spokesman said. 
</P>
