<TEXT>
<P>
Roger Kingdom won the gold medal in the 110-meter hurdles at the World 
University Games in Duisburg, West Germany, but cold weather and stiffness 
prevented the two-time Olympic champion from challenging his own world record. 
</P>
<P>
Kingdom's time of 13.26 was well outside his mark of 12.92. 
</P>
<P>
Americans also won three gold medals in relays on the final day of the Games, 
tying them with the Soviet Union for the lead with nine. 
</P>
