The Israeli military has drawn up a long-term plan that assumes its troops will 
still occupy the West Bank and Gaza Strip in the year 2000, an army spokeswoman 
said. She said the plan, to be presented to the Cabinet next week, envisages 
troops spending their entire three-year compulsory service in the territories, 
scene of a 20-month-old Palestinian uprising, instead of the current rotating 
tours of duty. Meanwhile, another Israeli army spokesman said the military is 
