</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There were no winning tickets chosen in Wednesday night's installment of the 
twice-weekly California "Lotto 6-49" game, so the $4.67-million jackpot will be 
added to Saturday's drawing, state lottery officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Saturday's jackpot will be an estimated $10 million. 
</P>
<P>
Eleven tickets had five of the six numbers chosen plus the bonus number, and 
each ticket is worth $117,953. There were 210 winners with five of six numbers. 
Each will receive $3,183. 
