<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
AILING QUARTERBACK OUT OF HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOULDER, Colo. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Colorado quarterback Sal Aunese, who is battling inoperable stomach and lung 
cancer, was released Wednesday from University Hospital in Denver after being 
admitted Monday night for treatment of a fever. 
</P>
<P>
Aunese, 21, was "doing fine," according to Dr. Wayne Gersoff, team physician. 
Gersoff said Aunese's temperature was near 101. "That's not catastrophically 
high, but for someone in his condition, it was high enough (to warrant 
hospitalization)," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Although growth of the tumor in Aunese's stomach has apparently slowed, Gersoff 
said Aunese's battle continues. He likened Aunese's fight for life to a 
three-way skirmish: the tumor versus his body, chemotherapy versus the tumor 
and the patient versus chemotherapy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
