<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
WILKINS TO GET $2.9 MILLION A YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATLANTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hawks star forward Dominique Wilkins has a new five-year $14.5-million contract 
that he says will allow him the peace of mind to "just go out and play ball." 
</P>
<P>
The contract, to be signed today, will pay the 29-year-old Wilkins an average 
of $2.9 million a year. Hawks President Stan Kasten agreed to set aside the 
remaining two years of Wilkins' current contract, which pays him $1.4 million a 
year. 
</P>
<P>
Wilkins, the Hawks' crowd favorite and leading scorer last season, had sought a 
salary of $3 million a year but said he has no problems accepting the lower 
deal. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm signing and I'm happy," Wilkins said. "I'm not complaining. I've got 
security. I think I did pretty good for a guy with two years left." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Dominique Wilkins 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
